.so z_name.so
.TH aegstate 5 \*(N)
.SH NAME
aegstate \- \*(n) state file
.SH SYNOPSIS
\f(CW/usr/local/lib/\*(n)/state\fP
.SH DESCRIPTION
The \*(n) state file
is used to store
the pointers to project directories.
.SH CONTENTS
.TP 8n
where = [{ ... }];
.br
This field is a table relating project name to project directory.
The structure is as follows:
.RS
.TP 8n
project_name = string;
.br
The name of a project.
.TP 8n
directory = string;
.br
Absolute path of the project's directory.
.RE
